    "She and Lee\u00a0travelled\u00a0across Europe visiting art museums and writing about how their bodies responded to the aesthetics of the various art pieces.": [],
    "According to Anstruther-Thomson, who dates are not always correct, she experienced an \"involuntary change of breathing\" in front of a painting which Lee took to be proof of their empathetic theory of art.": [],
    "In 1897, Anstruther-Thomson and Lee co-published their findings in \"Beauty and Ugliness,\" an article that focused on the physiology of aesthetics.": [],
